<div class="news">
<p class="newshead" lang="en"><b>Gentoo Weekly Newsletter -- 5 March 2007</b><br/><font size="0.90em">
      Posted on March 5, 2007
      by Chris Gianelloni</font></p>
<img class="newsicon" src="/images/icon-penguin.png" alt="tux"/><div class="newsitem">


<p>
<b>Opengear donates two CM4008, Xfce becomes an official project and more in
this week's <a href="/news/en/gwn/20070305-newsletter.xml">Gentoo Weekly
Newsletter</a>.</b> Coverage from FOSDEM, Chemnitzer Linux-Tage, and 
Linuxforum 07 events, as well as an interview with Gentoo developer <a href="mailto:nightmorph@gentoo.org">Joshua Saddler</a>. Also in this issue are the
usual security, bugs, and packages updates.

</p>

</div>
</div>
<div class="news">
<p class="newshead" lang="en"><b>Gentoo Weekly Newsletter -- 26 February 2007</b><br/><font size="0.90em">
      Posted on February 26, 2007
      by Chris Gianelloni</font></p>
<img class="newsicon" src="/images/icon-penguin.png" alt="tux"/><div class="newsitem">


<p>
<b>The GWN staff are seeking contributors, summaries from the gentoo-dev mailing
list, and more in this week's <a href="/news/en/gwn/20070226-newsletter.xml">Gentoo Weekly Newsletter</a>.</b>

Also in this issue, Gentoo in the press and the usual security, bugs, and
packages updates.
</p>

</div>
</div>
<div class="news">
<p class="newshead" lang="en"><b>Gentoo Weekly Newsletter -- 19 February 2007</b><br/><font size="0.90em">
      Posted on February 19, 2007
      by Chris Gianelloni</font></p>
<img class="newsicon" src="/images/icon-penguin.png" alt="tux"/><div class="newsitem">


<p>
<b>Upcoming changes to the ALSA packages and more in this week's <a href="/news/en/gwn/20070219-newsletter.xml">Gentoo Weekly
Newsletter</a>.</b> Also in this issue, Gentoo in the press and the usual
security, bugs, and packages updates.

</p>

</div>
</div>
<div class="news">
<p class="newshead" lang="en"><b>Gentoo Weekly Newsletter -- 12 February 2007</b><br/><font size="0.90em">
      Posted on February 12, 2007
      by Chris Gianelloni</font></p>
<img class="newsicon" src="/images/icon-penguin.png" alt="tux"/><div class="newsitem">


<p>
<b>Important time zone update information, testing wanted for new freetype
versions, some problems with NSS/NSPR, a thank you from the KDE team and more
in this week's <a href="/news/en/gwn/20070212-newsletter.xml">Gentoo Weekly
Newsletter</a>.</b> Don't miss a special thanks from the KDE team.

</p>

</div>
</div>
<div class="news">
<p class="newshead" lang="en"><b>Gentoo Weekly Newsletter -- 5 February 2007</b><br/><font size="0.90em">
      Posted on February 5, 2007
      by Chris Gianelloni</font></p>
<img class="newsicon" src="/images/icon-penguin.png" alt="tux"/><div class="newsitem">


<p>
<b>The KDE team is seeking your help, information about the upcoming removal of
mail-mta/qmail and more in this week's <a href="/news/en/gwn/20070205-newsletter.xml">Gentoo Weekly Newsletter</a>.</b>

Also in this week's GWN is the usual security, bugs, package updates, and
summaries from the community. Don't miss the interview with <a href="mailto:zzam@gentoo.org">Matthias Schwarzott</a>.
</p>

</div>
</div>
<div class="news">
<p class="newshead" lang="en"><b>Gentoo Weekly Newsletter -- 29 January 2007</b><br/><font size="0.90em">
      Posted on January 29, 2007
      by Chris Gianelloni</font></p>
<img class="newsicon" src="/images/icon-penguin.png" alt="tux"/><div class="newsitem">


<p>

<b>The long awaited Xfce 4.4 has been released and the Gentoo Forum Netherlands
celebrates its second anniversary in this week's <a href="/news/en/gwn/20070129-newsletter.xml">Gentoo Weekly Newsletter</a>.</b>
Also in this week's GWN is the usual security, bugs, and package updates and
summaries from the community.
</p>

</div>
